# Version Logging Requirement

**CRITICAL**: After making ANY changes to files, git, or deployment, you MUST invoke the version-logger skill.

## When to Invoke

Invoke `.cursor/skills/version-logger/SKILL.md` after:
- Creating, modifying, or deleting files
- Git commits or pushes
- SSH/deployment commands to production
- Database migrations
- Configuration changes

## How to Invoke

1. Complete your primary task
2. Read `.cursor/skills/version-logger/SKILL.md`
3. Follow the workflow to update:
   - `docs/master_log/Master_Log.md` (always)
   - `docs/master_log/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` (if files changed)
   - App Inventories (if code files/symbols changed): `Forge_Inventory.md`, `Apply_Inventory.md`, `Universalis_Inventory.md`, `Electracast_Inventory.md`, `Meridian_Inventory.md`
   - `README.md` (if public-facing changes)

## Quick Invocation

Provide this context to the version-logger:

```
Invoke version-logger:
- Type: [Feature|Fix|Refactor|Decision|Docs|Ops]
- Context: [Why this work happened]
- Summary: [What changed]
- Files: [List of files touched]
- Commands: [Commands run]
- Verification: [How verified]
- Apps affected: [forge|apply|universalis|electracast|meridian] (for Inventory updates)
```

## Do NOT Skip

Even for small changes, create a log entry. This maintains project history and keeps documentation current.
